    <h1 class="title is-1">Projects</h1>
    <div class="columns">
      <div class="column">
        <p>
          <em>Orbital</em> is a <strong
            >cross-platform real-time graphical rendering engine</strong
          > &amp;<strong> framework</strong> written in <strong>Rust</strong>.
          The goal of this project is to bridge well established <strong
            >industry-standard
          </strong>techniques with <strong>upcoming (next-gen)</strong> and <strong
            >experimental</strong
          > techniques to form a robust new foundation for <strong
            >next-gen visual computing</strong
          >. In some sense <em>Orbital</em> is a <strong
            >2D- &amp; 3D-Game Rendering Engine</strong
          >, but it can be used in countless more ways: from Computing to
          Offline Rendering to normal every day Apps. While the core language is <strong
            >Rust</strong
          >, almost any language can be used via the <strong
            >WebAssembly (WASM &amp; WASI)</strong
          > programming interface. The core is build on <strong>WGPU</strong>,
          which itself is an implementation of <strong>WebGPU</strong> and is used
          by modern browsers. <strong>WGPU</strong> acts as a <strong
            >Hardware Abstraction Layer</strong
          > for Orbital. For shading we utilize <strong>WGSL</strong>, a shading
          language specifically designed for <strong>WebGPU</strong>.<br /><br
          />Initially, this project was known under the name <em>Akimo</em> and originated
          in <strong>Java</strong> as a <strong>CPU-only</strong>
          <strong>2D- &amp; 3D-Rendering Engine</strong>. Eventually, it moved
          to LWJGL3 from <strong>OpenGL</strong> to <strong>Vulkan</strong>,
          then it was ported to <strong>C++</strong> with <strong>Vulkan</strong
          > and eventually arrived at <strong>Rust</strong> with initially <strong
            >Vulkan</strong
          >, later <strong>WGPU</strong>, where it was renamed to <em
            >Orbital</em
          >. I have been working on this project for years.
        </p>

